The paper deals with the problem of computing similarity between pairs of items in a streaming context, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The problem also has applications in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG), where similarity measures are often used. Finally, the paper introduces new indexing techniques, which is a topic in systems and networking (cs.SI).
